		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Fri, Mar 19th 8:35 AM2004 </span><span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=4&mid=107964214599650&num=5&page=0&post=1&replyto=107970322684718958"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=107970322684718958></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=61546"><span id="Sage">Slipskin</span></a><b><span id="Sage"><br>Sage</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />1262 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.07]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Slipskin&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>I don't even bother with macros.&nbsp;&nbsp;Too much trouble. Too easy to loose your sequence.  I prefer the tap-tap-tap method.  Also, I generally do a 3 song twist (rarely 4 if I use Amplification). <br /> <br />I have 3 hot key slots that I drag songs into from the spell bar. Tap once on the first song hot key to start my sequence. Tap twice on the second song hot key: the first tap stops the first song, the 2nd tap starts the second song.  Tap twice on the 3rd song hot key: again, the first tap stops the 2nd song, the 2nd tap starts the 3rd song.  Yes, its a lot of tapping. It has the advantage that if I have a missed note I don't have a significant break in my sequence (unless I have 3 missed notes in a row and a song drops).  Its extra work but not by much and I have more control.  If I need to break my sequence and throw in a different song its only a mouse click away. <br /> <br />How to set up a macro: <br /> <br />First, you need to create a hot key on your hot key pad (on the standard user interface that is in the lower left corner of your screen). Assuming you don't know how to create a custom hot key:  on the lower right of the screen is a window with several tabs.  One of those tabs looks like an oval.  If you look on that tab you will see a bunch of pre-configured short cut keys. Most of these you will never use (I never do).  Right click on one of those and a edit window will pop up.  In this window you can change the name of the key and its command lines. These command lines are the macros.  Go ahead and change the name to Song 1.  Down below on the first line erase the command that is there and type /stopsong . On the next line type /cast 1 . Now click on Done.  Left click and hold down your mouse button on the new Song 1 button you just made. This will cause the button to appear on your cursor. Now drag that over to an empty slot on your hot key pad on the lower left of your screen.  Click on the empty slot and the key should drop into place.  Congratulations! You have just made a hot key with a macro.  It will do 2 things whenever you click on it - stop whatever is the current song you are playing and then start playing the song that is in your 1st spell slot on your spells/songs bar.  Repeat this with 2 other keys using the other 2 songs you want to twist.  Now, here is the trick:  The hot keys on the lower left of your screen have numbers (0 thru 9).  These correspond to the number keys at the top of your standard keyboard.  Instead of clicking on them with the mouse just tap the number key on the keyboard with your finger. <br /> <br />The macro key you just made can be very elaborate. You have up to 6 command lines to play with.  Some bards will put all 3 songs on one hot key.  I don't like that since if you get a missed note you have to start the whole sequence from the first song. This means an important song may drop at at bad time.  But if you want to try it your 3 song twist on one key would look like this: <br /> <br />/stopsong <br />/cast 1 <br />/stopsong <br />/cast 2 <br />/stopsong <br />/cast 3 <br /> <br />Here is a list of commands/macros from this web site that will give you other ideas for macros:   <br /> <br /><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/game_Commands.htm" title="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/game_Commands.htm" target="akztarg">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/game_Commands.htm</a> <br /></p>
