		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=300017"><span id="">wuuvwen</span></a><b><span id=""></span></b><br />9 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=wuuvwen&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>I am a level 56 bard and started using macros back when I was in the 30's....I tried 2 and 3 song twists and finally realized there was more control and less fizzle restricting macros to a single song. Building the macro and tieing it to your hot keys allows for a single press of the key instead of the old double tap method.......I have found keeping 1 song per key and then using the hotkeys on page 1 to load all songs save 1 to turn attack on provides me the variety I need for doing Ldons and grouping in the zones. I also use 2 hot keys on the first page for other items other than songs. 1 is for assist and 1 is used as a Pull message to notify groups I am pulling a specific mob. When placing more than 1 song on a macro, I discovered that when lag is high, it is much harder to recover since you do not always start back at the first song......you may have to press button 4 or 5 times to cycle thru all strokes during a fizzle. Not ideal when in a fight....so leave it at one song macro per hot key and give yourself the variety to press any combination of keys depending on what keys you have your songs loaded into. Enjoy.</p>
